MOST IMMEDIATE
No.1/34/1/2011-Cab(i).
GOVERNMENT OF INDIA (BHARAT SARKAR)
CABINET SECRETARIAT (MANTRIMANDAL SACHIVALAYA)
New Delhi, the 19th May, 2011
The undersigned is directed to say that with effect from the 19th May, 2011:-
(i)
Km. Mamata Banerjee relinquished the charge of the office of the Minister
of Railways;
The Prime Minister assumed the charge of the office of the Minister of
Railways; and
Shri Mukul Roy, Minister of State in the Ministry of Shipping assumed the
additional charge of the office of the Minister of State in the Ministry of
Railways.
(ii)
(ii)
2.
The Ministry of Home Affairs may take further necessary action for issuing the
requisite Gazette Notification.
(K.L. Sharma)
